## 04 · Fake Plastic Trees
**Timecode IN:** `00:14:45:00`  **Timecode OUT:** `00:19:12:00`

| # | TC | Cue Name | Fixture Group | Action |
|---|-----|----------|---------------|--------|
| Q4.0 | 00:00 | Solo vocal | Single Robe DSC | Bare bulb look; one fixture, 3000K, no gel, 75% |
| Q4.1 | 00:52 | Acoustic guitar in | Add SL Robe | Second warm pool; subtle divergence, 60cm gap |
| Q4.2 | 01:48 | Band swell | GLP cyc bars | Deep violet from top; let it breathe, 30s in |
| Q4.3 | 02:38 | Emotional peak | All low fixtures | Kneeling wash; 15° angle; no overhead; blush pink |
| Q4.4 | 03:44 | Post-chorus drop | All to 0% except DSC spot | Silence = silence in light |
| Q4.5 | 04:10 | Outro build | All rig | Slow full-rig sunrise; 120s to 100%; warm white |
| Q4.6 | 19:12 | End | All | 8s fade; leave haze drifting 10s |

**Haze:** off during Q4.0–Q4.3. Enable at Q4.5 to catch the beam shafts in the build.  
**Follow-spots:** FOH A full show, FULL open iris — this is a close song.  
> This is usually the first moment the audience goes quiet. Don't ruin it. Trust the one lamp.

@plane z=4 label="05 — Just"
## 05 · Just
**Timecode IN:** `00:20:00:00`  **Timecode OUT:** `00:23:41:20`

| # | TC | Cue Name | Fixture Group | Action |
|---|-----|----------|---------------|--------|
| Q5.0 | 00:00 | Intro riff | GLP bars | Red hard-edge bars across stage; no wash |
| Q5.1 | 00:10 | Full band | Robe BMFL full | Grid snap to 90° tilt, all beams vertical; cyan |
| Q5.2 | 00:55 | Verse | GLP + Robe mix | Alternate red/cyan per beat; 4-beat cycle |
| Q5.3 | 01:28 | Chorus | All rig | Full intensity; fast CMY chase; 2Hz gobo spin |
| Q5.4 | 02:02 | Guitar break | Robe BMFL SR beam cluster | Tight aerial fan; white; 100% iris open |
| Q5.5 | 02:44 | "You do it to yourself" | All fixtures | Snap to full white; strobe 8Hz × 4 beats ONLY |
| Q5.6 | 03:10 | Final build | All | Increase strobe rate with each bar: 2→4→8→16Hz |
| Q5.7 | 23:41 | Hard stop | All | Frame-accurate blackout on last beat |

**Haze:** heavy from Q5.0. This is a beam song — feed the haze machine.  
**Follow-spots:** BOTH FOH + balcony on Thom. Fast iris work. Thom moves a lot — warn operators: stay tight.  
> Epilepsy warning was issued at house open. Strobe sequence at Q5.6 is cleared by venue.  
> **Q5.7 must be frame-accurate.** Set as a hard chase cue in grandMA, NOT a manual go.

@plane z=5 label="06 — Street Spirit"
## 06 · Street Spirit (Fade Out)
**Timecode IN:** `00:38:00:00`  **Timecode OUT:** `00:42:48:00`

| # | TC | Cue Name | Fixture Group | Action |
|---|-----|----------|---------------|--------|
| Q6.0 | 00:00 | Arpeggiated intro | All to 0% | Complete darkness; let audience settle |
| Q6.1 | 00:08 | Melody enters | Single pinspot on Thom | 1% intensity; build to 12% over 30s; NO colour |
| Q6.2 | 01:00 | First lyric | Add single cyc uplight | Deep blue 0/0/180; 5% intensity only |
| Q6.3 | 02:15 | Chorus | GLP bars top | Slow blue drip from top; 60s total fade; 0→40% |
| Q6.4 | 03:20 | "Immerse your soul in love" | All rig | 90s slow fade to full deep blue; let it breathe |
| Q6.5 | 04:10 | Final repeat | Robe BMFL slow tilt | Beams begin drift from vertical; 2°/s; imperceptible |
| Q6.6 | 04:48 | End | All | Fade to 0% over final note; 4s |
| Q6.7 | 04:52 | House lights | FOH | Slow house to 20%; hold for applause |

**Haze:** off entirely. The column of smoke in the one pinspot IS the effect.  
**Follow-spots:** FOH A only. Iris to minimum. No colour correction frame.  
> This is the closer. The whole show is for this song. Less is everything.  
> After Q6.7, walk the stage in the dark and check: *did we earn it?*
